[assistant] Fixed the Maven SCM 2.2.1 test compile issue in:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/org.apache.maven.scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/2.2.1/src/test/java/org_apache_maven_scm/maven_scm_provider_gitexe/GitExeCommandLineConstructionTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - Stopped calling `GitTagCommand.createCommandLine(...)`, which is package-private in 2.2.1.
[assistant] - Exercised tag command construction through the supported public API:
[assistant]   - `GitTagCommand.executeTagCommand(...)`
[assistant]   - `ScmTagParameters.setSignOption(...)`
[assistant] - Kept functional coverage by initializing a temporary git repository and verifying:
[assistant]   - default tag creation succeeds
[assistant]   - `FORCE_NO_SIGN` produces `--no-sign` and succeeds even with `tag.gpgSign=true`
[assistant]   - tag push command construction is still checked through the public instance method
[assistant] - Added bounded git process execution with a 30-second timeout.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the tests locally, per instruction.
[assistant-event] text_end
