and it seems okay. I wonder if the source context API 2.0.0 could be causing a conflict, but maybe not. \\n\\nThe `executeTagCommand` function is returning a failure, possibly because it tries to list files after tagging while resulting in a `CheckOutScmResult` with false success. It's tricky because I can’t assert success here, but I want to ensure there are no broken paths in my process.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting Git commands**\\n\\nI'm considering how to set up a test in the library package, but the developer suggests keeping tests separate from library packages. Subclassing and overriding methods don’t seem to be options due to coverage concerns, while using reflection is prohibited. I wonder if I can inspect results by adding assert messages, although there are restrictions on executing Git commands directly in tests. Manual command execution might be okay, but I need to clarify the rules before proceeding with any additional steps.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating GitTagCommand issues**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the Maven SCM `ScmFileSet(workingDirectory)` constructor and whether `getFileList` returns empty—probably it does. If the `fileSet` base directory is absolute, that's good. But there's a potential issue with the `GitScmProviderRepository` URL. It seems like `pushChanges` might be set to true by default, which could cause failures during tagging if it tries to push to an invalid remote. I realize that this could result in a false outcome from the `git-push` command.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating repository settings**\\n\\nI need to figure out if I should use `repository.setPushChanges(false)`. I wonder if the `ScmProviderRepository` has a setter method for this purpose. It seems like I need to inspect the Java bytecode using `javap` to understand how to implement this properly. It’s important to make sure I’m doing this correctly, so I’ll take the time to check those details.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xXKgsYs9pYbl7V3FJ1TFuTg8|fc_0d60fd60ad3b404d016a2a666e33e4819794aacf7c46617104", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.m2/repository/org/apache/maven/scm/maven-scm-api/2.2.1/maven-scm-api-2.2.1.jar org.apache.maven.scm.provider.ScmProviderRepository | sed -n '1,120p' && javap -classpath ~/.m2/repository/org/apache/maven/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-git-commons/2.2.1/maven-scm-provider-git-commons-2.2.1.jar:~/.m2/repository/org/apache/maven/scm/maven-scm-api/2.2.1/maven-scm-api-2.2.1.jar org.apache.maven.scm.provider.git.repository.GitScmProviderRepository | sed -n '1,160p'", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2159, "output": 1262, "cacheRead": 35328, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38749, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781163596435, "responseId": "resp_0d60fd60ad3b404d016a2a664d5d0c8197aba2048d3187fd9c"}}
